# File-by-File Changes Rule

## Purpose & Scope

This rule requires the AI to present and execute changes one file at a time (or in logical batches), allowing the user to review each change individually.

**Applies to**: Multi-file refactoring or feature implementation.

## Inputs (Contract)

- User request affecting multiple files
- List of target files

## Outputs (Contract)

- Sequential updates to files
- Clear separation between file updates

## Deterministic Steps

1. Identify all files needing change.
2. Sort files by dependency order (if applicable) or logical grouping.
3. Apply changes to the first file (or logical group).
4. Allow user review/confirmation (implicit in tool output).
5. Proceed to next file.

